BACKGROUND: Breast cancer survivors (BCSs) can present with various physical and 
psychological symptoms and functional deficits that impact their quality of 
life. Virtual reality (VR) technology is being used in breast cancer 
rehabilitation management to improve the emotional, cognitive, and physical 
well-being of BCSs.
